==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[besprengan|besprenġan]], corresponding to [[be-]] + [[sprenge]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/bɪˈsprɛnʤ/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|besprenges|besprenging|besprent}}

# ''(obsolete except as past participle adjective)'' To [[sprinkle]] or [[scatter]] with.
#:*'''1973''': his ample mush was pleated with fat, wormed with the great pox and so '''besprent''' with whelks, bubukles and burst capillaries that it seemed like a contour map of the Trossachs. — Kyril Bonfiglioli, ''Don't Point That Thing at Me'' (Penguin 2001, p. 78)